==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Arcuation
<hw>Arc`u*a"tion</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>arcuatio</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of bending or
curving; incurvation; the state of being bent; crookedness.</def>
<rj><au>Coxe.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Hort.)</fld> <def>A mode of propagating trees by
bending branches to the ground, and covering the small shoots with
earth; layering.</def> <rj><au>Chambers.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Arcubalist</ent>⟦br⟧
